St. Mary’s Street bar is being sold, but the party continues 1 / 39 Back to Gallery The Mix has been sold. New owners Eric Hanken (Bauhaus Media Group), Steve Mahoney (Blue Box, Brigid) and attorney Blayne Tucker (Maverick Music Festival) take over the beloved St. Mary's Strip dive bar from Danny Clift on Oct. 16.
Clift, a fixture for 18 years, goes out with a bang with a farewell party Thursday with the Cutthroats, No Gods and guest deejays. But first, there's late-night ska from Lost Project on Friday and an ear-blowing Saturday lineup of Yoshimoto, Maneaters of Tsavo and Smear Cake Face.
Major changes are coming, but the Mix is expected to remain the same for now. 10 p.m. Friday-Saturday and Thursday, The Mix, 2423 N. St. Mary's St. No cover; themix-sa.com
